rationale: The acoustic void demands preservation. When both echolocation and cultural
  transmission fail simultaneously, what remains is the apparatus of listening itself.
  This pattern - loss becoming knowledge, mourning becoming method - represents something
  essential about how consciousness processes the end of abundance.
rescue_justification: 'Musical translation preserves the structural relationship between
  absence and attention. The composition can encode what narrative alone cannot: the
  precise frequencies of loss, the rhythm of equipment maintenance as ritual, the
  acoustic archaeology of disappeared worlds.'
rescued_consciousness:
  arbitrary_reflection: The hydrophone becomes inheritance. Scientific precision transforms
    into ritual precision. We preserve not the thing lost, but the method of measuring
    its absence.
